<subSubSection id="17ABA5A2EA3B0C2EFF1CFC9AF5535694" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" type="type_taxon">
<paragraph id="5F0EF629EA3B0C2EFF1CFC9AF2665071" blockId="36.[151,1436,843,1566]" box="[151,788,843,870]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis id="6DC52A3BEA3B0C2EFF1CFC9AF0495072" bold="true" box="[151,315,843,869]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<typeStatus id="800A488BEA3B0C2EFF1CFC9AF1A65072" box="[151,212,843,869]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Type</typeStatus>
species:
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="98B18DAAEA3B0C2EFEC8FC9DF2635071" authority="Crotch, 1874: 74" authorityName="Crotch" authorityPageNumber="74" authorityYear="1874" box="[323,785,844,870]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Hydnobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="matthewsi">
<emphasis id="6DC52A3BEA3B0C2EFEC8FC9DF3325072" box="[323,576,844,869]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Hydnobius matthewsi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="3B208BD8EA3B0C2EFDCCFC9DF2635071" author="Crotch, G. R." box="[583,785,844,870]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" pagination="73 - 80" refId="ref29508" refString="Crotch, G. R. (1874) Descriptions of New Species of Coleoptera from the Pacific Coast of the United States. Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 5, 73 - 80." type="journal article" year="1874">Crotch, 1874: 74</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5F0EF629EA3B0C2EFF4DFCA3F22257D5" blockId="36.[151,1436,843,1566]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis id="6DC52A3BEA3B0C2EFF4DFCA3F094509B" bold="true" box="[198,486,882,908]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Diagnostic description.</emphasis>
Body large, elongate, length of pronotum + elytra = 3.1–6.4 mm; antennal club interrupted 5-segmented; mandibles elongate, broad at base and narrow apically, apices entire; labrum emarginate; clypeus strongly sclerotized; epistomal suture clearly indicated laterally, usually faintly visible medially; eyes relatively small, weakly or not protuberant; post-ocular tempora not developed; gular sutures widely separated basally and apically, convergent near middle; no suture separating gula from submentum (except in 
<taxonomicName id="98B18DAAEA3B0C2EFE9EFBE5F0DC575A" authorityName="Peck &amp; Cook" authorityYear="2009" baseAuthorityName="Brown" baseAuthorityYear="1932" box="[277,430,1076,1101]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Macrohydnobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simulator">
<emphasis id="6DC52A3BEA3B0C2EFE9EFBE5F0DC575A" box="[277,430,1076,1101]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">M. simulator</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); pronotum with sub-basal impressed line or row of punctures; mesoventrite weakly oblique, not carinate (except in 
<taxonomicName id="98B18DAAEA3B0C2EFD8CFB8AF3EC5763" authorityName="Peck &amp; Cook" authorityYear="2009" baseAuthorityName="Brown" baseAuthorityYear="1932" box="[519,670,1115,1140]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Macrohydnobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simulator">
<emphasis id="6DC52A3BEA3B0C2EFD8CFB8AF3EC5763" box="[519,670,1115,1140]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">M. simulator</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); mesocoxae narrowly separated by mesoventral and metaventral processes; outer margin of male protibia prolonged beyond base of tarsi; male protibia with elongate, sinuate apical spur; femora lack distinct teeth on posterior margins.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5F0EF629EA3B0C2EFF4DFB1FF5535694" blockId="36.[151,1436,843,1566]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
The following characters of 
<taxonomicName id="98B18DAAEA3B0C2EFD92FB1EF3AC57FF" authorityName="Peck &amp; Cook" authorityYear="2009" box="[537,734,1231,1256]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Macrohydnobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6DC52A3BEA3B0C2EFD92FB1EF3AC57FF" box="[537,734,1231,1256]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Macrohydnobius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
separate this genus from 
<taxonomicName id="98B18DAAEA3B0C2EFB98FB1EF5E057FF" authorityName="Schmidt" authorityYear="1841" box="[1043,1170,1231,1256]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Hydnobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6DC52A3BEA3B0C2EFB98FB1EF5E057FF" box="[1043,1170,1231,1256]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Hydnobius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: body large, length of pronotum + elytra = 3.1–6.4 mm; mandibles elongate with apices entire (bidentate in 
<taxonomicName id="98B18DAAEA3B0C2EFB1EFB24F4675619" authorityName="Schmidt" authorityYear="1841" box="[1173,1301,1269,1294]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Hydnobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6DC52A3BEA3B0C2EFB1EFB24F4675619" box="[1173,1301,1269,1294]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Hydnobius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); lacking a suture separating gula from submentum (present in 
<taxonomicName id="98B18DAAEA3B0C2EFC8AFACDF2F35622" authorityName="Schmidt" authorityYear="1841" box="[769,897,1308,1333]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Hydnobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6DC52A3BEA3B0C2EFC8AFACDF2F35622" box="[769,897,1308,1333]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Hydnobius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); pronotum with sub-basal impressed line or row of punctures; male protibia with elongate, sinuate apical spur (lacking in 
<taxonomicName id="98B18DAAEA3B0C2EFBCDFA92F5B5564B" authorityName="Schmidt" authorityYear="1841" box="[1094,1223,1347,1372]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Hydnobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6DC52A3BEA3B0C2EFBCDFA92F5B5564B" box="[1094,1223,1347,1372]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Hydnobius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); femora without distinct teeth on posterior margins (metafemoral tooth present in 
<taxonomicName id="98B18DAAEA3B0C2EFC1AFAB8F5625695" authorityName="Schmidt" authorityYear="1841" box="[913,1040,1385,1410]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Hydnobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6DC52A3BEA3B0C2EFC1AFAB8F5625695" box="[913,1040,1385,1410]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Hydnobius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="17ABA5A2EA3B0C2EFF4DFA5EF46356C7" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="5F0EF629EA3B0C2EFF4DFA5EF46356C7" blockId="36.[151,1436,843,1566]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis id="6DC52A3BEA3B0C2EFF4DFA5EF36256BE" bold="true" box="[198,528,1423,1449]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Distribution and diversity.</emphasis>
The genus is known to contain only the following Nearctic species. We have not been able to recognize that any existing Palearctic species should be placed in this new genus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="17ABA5A2EA3B0C2EFF4DFA0CF06F5509" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="5F0EF629EA3B0C2EFF4DFA0CF06F5509" blockId="36.[151,1436,843,1566]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis id="6DC52A3BEA3B0C2EFF4DFA0CF02156E0" bold="true" box="[198,339,1501,1527]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Etymology.</emphasis>
From the Greek 
<emphasis id="6DC52A3BEA3B0C2EFD91FA0CF31D56E1" box="[538,623,1501,1526]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">macros</emphasis>
, long; refers to the elongate shape and large size of these beetles; and 
<taxonomicName id="98B18DAAEA3B0C2EFF1CF9D5F064550A" authorityName="Schmidt" authorityYear="1841" box="[151,278,1540,1565]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Hydnobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6DC52A3BEA3B0C2EFF1CF9D5F064550A" box="[151,278,1540,1565]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Hydnobius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
